content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and block dictionary to help you construct this building.

Analysis of Target Structure:
- 3 layers in total
- Bottom layer: 3 orange cylindrical blocks on 2 yellow rectangular base blocks
- Middle layer: 1 yellow rectangular block connecting the bottom columns
- Top layer: 1 red arched/curved block with a peaked roof section

Block Selection:
- Bottom layer:
  - Yellow rectangular blocks (index 6 and 8)
  - Orange cylindrical blocks (index 10 and 11)
- Middle layer:
  - Yellow rectangular block (index 7)
- Top layer:
  - Red curved/arched block with peaked roof (index 2)

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 6 (yellow rectangular block)
    Step2: Move block with index 8 (yellow rectangular block)
    Step3: Move block with index 10 (orange cylindrical block)
    Step4: Move block with index 11 (orange cylindrical block)
    Step5: Move block with index 10 (another orange cylindrical block)
    Step6: Move block with index 7 (yellow rectangular block)
    Step7: Move block with index 2 (red curved/arched block)
}
